text: Tracks all my moods, prescriptions, and room for random thoughts. Gives time for each entry. As mood changes I am able to record when and how long. I am also able to add or delete  emotions and prescriptions as needed.Very user friendly and simple ui.. Best tracking app I have tried. Only thing I would add would be a dark theme.

I like this app a lot. It is easy to use.  I like that you can change the color of the moods, I've set my favorite as positive and my least as negative. It really helps me rate my mood. I also like that there are so many moods to chose from! And the note section is really helpful. I recommend this for people with depression, anxiety or if you just want a mood journal. Five stars.

Would be better if the menus for (moods) symptoms and medications allowed you to type it in and it would search for it. I find it a pain to have to scroll through my whole list. Besides that it is exactly what I needed.

Lots of moods to choose from, can add ypur own, tracks medication and drug use, and you can use it to track things like panic attacks, psychosis, mania, self-harm... Doesn't analyse much but its really useful for self-observation.

It is a great way to track your mood and the best one that both me and my therapist liked. The only thing I would like is a option to have a reminder more than just 3 times a week, I feel like that could help me a lot.

I love this app mainly because it has one feature I couldn't find anywhere: it has more than 5 moods AND they are well described + customisable. One thing that really bothers me: the mood colours. Best case scenario - if I could set a colour for each tag, but if not, I wish "black" would be an option (for bad mood), or green-blue to go with yellow-red Edit: thanks for answering and taking my suggestions seriously! What also popped into my mind is that the text (note) is vertical, which makes no sense, because it takes a lot of space and is basically unreadable. Just try typing a note w/ 140 characters (size of a tweet) and you'll see what I mean.
replyText:
Thanks for using Mood log and for the feedback!
I see how having more color options, and colors associated with tags could be really helpful. I'm going to look into adding more color flexibility in a future update.

Thanks again!
Sincerely,
Andrew

text: Good app. for tracking moods over time, allowing more accurate reporting trio your health professional than mere memory. Great that you can add your own adjectives etc to describe mods and feelings.
It does what it says. Some better visualization of the data and layout of the data entry would dress it up better but I can't complain for free. Ads are unobtrusive, a small bar at the bottom.
I have BPD and it's a simple and easy way of tracking changing moods throughout the day. I particularly like how you can personalise the moods and the format of the graph. Good app
Really love it. It's extremely helpful! I have mine set to ask me 3 times a day. I've learned a lot about myself by using this app.
It is a very user friendly app, quite flexible to track mood and meds. I would give 5 if to get the logs were easier.
Nice mood tracker. Easy to use. Easy to customize. I have a question, if I have the upgraded version am I able to print out the graph?
replyText:
Thanks for using Mood Log and for the kind words!
No, the upgraded version let's export your records as a spreadsheet. The records you're viewing are the ones that will be printed out.

Sincerely,
Andrew

text: Very simple design, but the user interface is a bit hard to navigate. Otherwise I'd give five stars.
I have bipolar so thought this will be a good app to use to see a visual of possible triggers.
It's a great app! My only suggestion would be to add custom colors options.
replyText:
Thanks for using Mood Log and for the kind words!
In the Settings there are a couple options for customizing the positive and negative colors. I also see how having more color customization could be even better and I'll look into adding that in a future update.

Thanks for the feedback!
Sincerely,
Andrew

text: Great mood log app. Very useful. Love it!'
A very basic app with limited input and output
Great for tracking moods
It's so simple and easy
Great app!
helps me reflect
Love it because it helps
Easy to use.
Cool

Overall, this is a great app to use. The only minor complaint that I have is that it would be nice if the emotions had some kind of emoji or sticker attached to it. Its a nice way to visualize your moods as well. Also I feel it would give some people more incentive to stay on top of keeping track in addition to having the chart. Maybe have a chart that has the emojis on it so you can keep track of your moods that way.

Very good for tracking my emotions and moods. Was actually recommend to me by my therapist so I could see when I happened to hit any sort of depressed period in time. Has helped me get my emotions back onto a healthy track, thankful that an app like this exists.

I never write reviews but I am for this. I love it! Simple way to track my mood and I can make notes about what I was doing or thinking at that time. I also use the medications tab to track things like sleep and nicotine/alcohol consumption. In the tags I track my moods, where I am (work, home, ect.), and how bad my schizo symptoms are. I love it!

Great potential..needs a few updates.. 1)trigger button. Every time a trigger situation is encountered..to be able to input that would be a huge help! 2) would love to add diet components... Alcohol for example 3) interface isn't intuitive.  Great start for a potentially life altering product.

It's not clear which end of the scale is good. Is it blue or red? Am I rating my happiness or sadness? ---ok thanks for pointing out the settings! I changed the review. I actually tried three apps, but this one is private, and easier than others.
replyText:
Thanks for trying Mood Log!
I left the scale open so that users can choose what they like best. I like to consider 0 as the worst possible mood and 10 as the best possible. There are also options for different scale colors in the settings.

Sincerely,
Andrew

text: I love this app - it's simple and useful and doesn't leave much to be desired. However, one small thing kept me from rating it five stars: I have been using this app to track the way my meds affect me emotionally throughout the day (in addition to long-term). Since I'm creating new entries three times a day if not more, it would be nice if there was some kind of zoom feature on the graph so you could track your mood over a single day or two, instead of a whole week (at the least). That way it would be easier to notice mood patterns based on the time of day. Other than that, this app is perfect and exactly what I was looking for. Thank you, Mood Log!
replyText:
Thanks for using Mood log and for the kind words!
I see how being able to view moods over a shorter period of time could be really useful for seeing daily patterns. I'm going to look into adding that in one of the many updates I have planned for Mood Log's future.

Thanks for the feedback!
Sincerely,
Andrew

text: Great app. Has helped me keep track of my different mood swings and length of my hipo manic and depresed episodes.

After looking through tonnes of apps I felt this suited me best. It has a bunch of options that if you customise correctly can be much more comprehensive than any other offering. I use two numbering scales, one, the default for grading my mood, the other I put in tags to grade my energy levels. I use the medications option to keep track of sleep, exercise, space etc since I am not on medication. The statistics display is also better than some more popular apps. For me this is the best app available as I mentioned.
This app has been wonderful! I have wanted to monitor my mood for a while but forget to write it down. With the reminder on my phone it's awesome and so easy!
I love it!  Helps me keep track of my mood swings daily and even few times daily.

Ideal for tracking moods/thoughts, I really like the fact that you can create your own mood tags. App is nice and simple. The one downside is that you can only set a maximum of 3 reminders a day, if it could be amended so that you can set as many reminders as you want, I'd give it 5 stars.
My therpasist wanted me tho start tracking my moods tip see when and what triggered my depression and of all the apps i have tried out this ones covers all the points i need to track
i've been trying to find a good app for tracking moods;; this one i highly recommend! i don't think i'll be uninstalling this one anytime soon.

Love that you can make notes. Also like the interactive moods you can add to their list to make it more personal. Also love the chart it gives a good visual of what some have a hard time figuring out. Thanks! üëçüëçüëç
This app really helps when you have depression and anxiety. I really like it!
Overall good app. Great to track with notes and spot trends. Would love to have a greater range to work with, such as the reviewer's suggestion to add trigger info, etc.
